snippet: Norwegian swimmer Alexander Dale Oen, the world 100 meters breaststroke champion, died of hereditary heart disease, an Arizona medical examiner said on Tuesday.
abstract: Arizona medical examiner concludes that Norwegian swimmer Alexander Dale Oen, who collapsed at training camp in April, died of hereditary heart disease.
lead_paragraph: Norwegian swimmer Alexander Dale Oen, the world 100 meters breaststroke champion, died of hereditary heart disease, an Arizona medical examiner said on Tuesday.

headline.seo: Norwegian Swimming Champion Dale Oen Died of Heart Disease
headline.main: Heart Disease Blamed in Death of Norwegian Swimmer
